body.description: G.I. Joe is a highly skilled, on-demand, special operations force of men and women from around the globe. tasked with defending the world from Cobra, a ruthless criminal organization bent on total domination. The brave members of G.I. Joe are prepared to seek out Cobra in any environment on the planet. From hostile jungles to ice-clad arctic peaks…wherever there’s trouble, G.I. Joe is there. New to the G.I. Joe Classified Series line, Robert "Grunt" Graves comes ready for adventure, with multiple points of articulation for high poseability. This Robert "Grunt" Graves figure contains 8 character-inspired accessories including 2 helmets, knife, backpack, fold-down team awareness device, and 3 weapon accessories; plus a footlocker to stow all his gear! "Grunt is a highly motivated, systematic individual. He's a stand-up guy who doesn't blow his cool in a fire-fight." G.I. Joe and all related characters are trademarks of Hasbro.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The surprising true star of this release wave
reviews.reviewText: I got grunt along with LowLight and Tunnel Rat. I fully expected Grunt to be the weakest of the 3. Boy was I wrong. He's fantastic.While he basically uses Stalkers body with a rubber Plate Carrier armor overlay, it looks good. He has amazing detail He comes with 2 rifles which attach to his backpack. A NATO issue M=16 classic weapon and the official GI Joe Laser Rifle from the Sunbow Cartoon. His loadout includes a knife and what I assume is his Gameboy 3Ds strapped to his chest so he can find pokemon on his long marches.And Grunt include an extra head. A game changing piece. A Green and Gold Steele Corp head. This means Grunt is GI Joes forst ever mainline Army Builder. You can have Robert Grunt Graves (Later Lt. Robert Grunt Graves) leading a squad of 2 or 4 non flying Ground Steel Corp squad The only downside is to army build him you need to remove his name tag and dummy up some other name for each.Be warned the Green and Gold Steel Corp Helmet that comes with Grunt does not fit the STeel Corp figures that come in the 2 pack. Nor do those helmets fit Grunt. The Green and Gold STeel Brigade Grunt Helmet does fit the Valaverse Steel Brigade figures..Grunt looks a little dull at first. But you quickly realise that he forms the centerpiece of your GI Joe Team. (Original 13 4evar!)Edit; Just a slightly mild negative followup. I ended up getting 2 more Grunts and an extra Stalker to use as part of my Steel Corps. They look good in a group especially alongside the steel Corp Jetpack 2 pack. I actually like the green fatigue look better than the blue and tan. But the one thing I notice with the 2 latest Grunt figures is I can see that the "Stalker" body mold that these figures all use, is starting to show signs of wearing out. The Bicep Rotation Joints on both figures seem to be very gappy and have a hard time staying together. So buyers be warned you may see some gapping at those joints.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice throwback to the original
reviews.reviewText: My first Joe as a kid. Great weapons and accessories with a color scheme that’s a nod to the original. Except the thumbs don’t immediately break off like the original.Paint apps great.The 3/4 helmet felt off because 1) not as detailed as the rest of the gear. 2) it’s a different shade of green than the uniform. But if you think about it, irl those two things are made from different materials so it makes sense. The Steel Brigade/Corps.full face one more than makes up for it.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice to have good guy army builder figures!
reviews.reviewText: The price is a bit steep, but I'm excited for 2 things: the original rifle from the cartoon that has the same appearance, the fact it comes with a Steel Corp. helmet in there makes it the perfect army builder. So great to have good guys for once! All my other armies have been of evil dudes! These really fill in the gaps to make your army filled out. Especially once the Steel Corp 2 pack comes out!
